        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 2:59PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 257 PM EDT, a trained weather spotter reported a strong
thunderstorm producing pea size hail just northwest of Willis,
moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Trained weather spotter.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Floyd...
Willis...
and Alum Ridge.
</description>
        <instruction>Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</instruction>
